A bodyguard attached to Embu governor Martin Wambora has been killed after an alleged brawl with bodaboda riders. Â Its said that the deceased Christopher Njue was seeking boda boda transport services from Kithimu in Manyatta to embu and disagreed with the operators over payment leading to a fierce fight. Njue sucumbed to his injuries at Embu level 5 hospital where he had been taken for treatment. Police in Embu are already investigating the incident. The governor's aide had earlier been rescued by police officers who were on patrol and rushed him to the health facility but he died moments later.